1
00:00:12,512 --> 00:00:15,546
(Seven years ago)

2
00:00:27,160 --> 00:00:29,760
Mr. Li, I want to buy medicine.

3
00:00:30,760 --> 00:00:32,039
You only give me one copper coin?

4
00:00:33,359 --> 00:00:34,640
Captain Liu, I'm sorry.

5
00:00:34,920 --> 00:00:36,000
I just had a big meal

6
00:00:36,159 --> 00:00:38,439
in the market.

7
00:00:38,600 --> 00:00:40,799
And I only have one copper coin left.

8
00:00:42,960 --> 00:00:44,159
You ate it up?

9
00:00:44,960 --> 00:00:45,640
Yeah.

10
00:00:46,600 --> 00:00:48,960
Didn't you think
of leaving me some food?

11
00:00:51,359 --> 00:00:52,960
Captain Liu, can you tell me

12
00:00:53,159 --> 00:00:54,840
what exactly is going on in Yanyu Tower?

13
00:00:55,119 --> 00:00:55,840
If you want food,

14
00:00:56,079 --> 00:00:57,359
that's no problem.

15
00:00:57,520 --> 00:00:59,079
I can buy it for you every day.

16
00:00:59,439 --> 00:01:01,200
Why are you asking about this?

17
00:01:01,626 --> 00:01:02,707
I have a friend studying

18
00:01:02,867 --> 00:01:04,666
in Yanyu Tower.

19
00:01:05,306 --> 00:01:06,226
Recently,

20
00:01:06,627 --> 00:01:09,026
there has been a lot of gossip
about Lin Rulan's case.

21
00:01:09,186 --> 00:01:10,067
And I'm worried.

22
00:01:10,507 --> 00:01:12,746
Lin Rulan won't win.

23
00:01:14,186 --> 00:01:16,386
Don't get involved in this.

24
00:01:18,907 --> 00:01:19,746
Forget it.

25
00:01:20,067 --> 00:01:21,547
If you don't tell me, I'm leaving.

26
00:01:24,267 --> 00:01:25,186
Mr. Li.

27
00:01:25,987 --> 00:01:26,946
Li Chunfeng.

28
00:01:27,707 --> 00:01:28,746
You pickpocket.

29
00:01:30,226 --> 00:01:32,106
I've helped you a lot in the past.

30
00:01:32,267 --> 00:01:33,427
Now I'm in trouble,

31
00:01:33,826 --> 00:01:35,386
and you only give me one copper coin?

32
00:01:35,627 --> 00:01:37,147
Do you have a conscience?

33
00:03:04,808 --> 00:03:09,864
=Faithful=
(Adapted from the novel "Faithful")

34
00:03:10,386 --> 00:03:14,034
=Episode 13, Chapter 7, Part 1=
(Lin Rulan's Red Wedding Dress)

35
00:03:14,075 --> 00:03:16,690
(Lin's Pharmacy)

36
00:03:34,706 --> 00:03:36,920
Rulan, I got you something to eat.

37
00:03:41,146 --> 00:03:43,667
You really acted impulsively.

38
00:03:44,187 --> 00:03:45,306
Tell me the truth.

39
00:03:46,507 --> 00:03:48,827
Do you have feelings for Mr. Wu?

40
00:03:49,387 --> 00:03:50,986
That's why

41
00:03:51,266 --> 00:03:52,440
you had intimate relations

42
00:03:53,266 --> 00:03:54,426
with him?

43
00:03:55,666 --> 00:03:57,625
You're afraid
of being blamed by our parents.

44
00:03:58,226 --> 00:03:59,905
So you made up it all.

45
00:04:01,185 --> 00:04:02,346
What if I say yes?

46
00:04:02,506 --> 00:04:03,705
How could you be so silly?

47
00:04:04,145 --> 00:04:05,386
If you had told the truth earlier,

48
00:04:05,786 --> 00:04:07,465
things wouldn't have ended up like this.

49
00:04:09,185 --> 00:04:10,185
What would happen then?

50
00:04:11,145 --> 00:04:12,786
Our parents
and I would stand up for you.

51
00:04:13,226 --> 00:04:14,585
We would make Wu Lian

52
00:04:14,786 --> 00:04:15,625
take responsibility.

53
00:04:15,786 --> 00:04:16,625
At least,

54
00:04:19,385 --> 00:04:22,586
it could be resolved quietly,

55
00:04:23,265 --> 00:04:24,986
instead of ruining your reputation.

56
00:04:25,625 --> 00:04:27,026
What are you going to do?

57
00:04:27,825 --> 00:04:29,786
You are muddle-headed.

58
00:04:30,666 --> 00:04:32,745
I'm tired, brother.

59
00:04:34,546 --> 00:04:35,505
You can leave.

60
00:04:40,425 --> 00:04:41,265
Rulan.

61
00:04:43,265 --> 00:04:44,385
I'm worried about you.

62
00:04:45,305 --> 00:04:46,425
I spoke a little harshly.

63
00:04:46,865 --> 00:04:47,945
Don't take it to heart.

64
00:04:50,265 --> 00:04:51,226
Eat something.

65
00:04:51,986 --> 00:04:52,865
I'll go.

66
00:05:10,865 --> 00:05:13,026
(Gentle Breeze)
That matter has been resolved.

67
00:05:13,505 --> 00:05:15,865
You just focus on
preparing the embroidery.

68
00:05:16,945 --> 00:05:17,706
Yes.

69
00:05:36,505 --> 00:05:38,305
This is your new product?

70
00:05:38,706 --> 00:05:39,786
It's hot in summer.

71
00:05:40,106 --> 00:05:42,906
It's made of fine gauze,
cooling the skin.

72
00:05:43,505 --> 00:05:45,106
It's custom made for you.

73
00:05:57,745 --> 00:05:59,666
Her Majesty has decided

74
00:06:00,106 --> 00:06:02,146
the gift list for the tributaries.

75
00:06:02,945 --> 00:06:05,185
Yanyu Embroidery is listed.

76
00:06:05,745 --> 00:06:07,625
Congratulations.

77
00:06:08,346 --> 00:06:10,505
It can be attributed
to your recommendation.

78
00:06:10,865 --> 00:06:12,146
This batch of embroidery

79
00:06:12,505 --> 00:06:15,385
concerns the reputation of the court.

80
00:06:16,026 --> 00:06:17,906
I have strongly recommended it.

81
00:06:18,825 --> 00:06:20,706
You mustn't make any mistakes.

82
00:06:20,906 --> 00:06:21,906
Madam, you can rest assured.

83
00:06:22,666 --> 00:06:25,385
When has Yanyu Tower ever let you down?

84
00:06:47,146 --> 00:06:50,385
Wan, don't blame me.

85
00:06:50,986 --> 00:06:52,706
We can't fight them.

86
00:06:54,305 --> 00:06:56,625
Eat the medicine.

87
00:07:12,986 --> 00:07:13,865
Mother.

88
00:07:15,666 --> 00:07:16,786
Anything is bland to me,

89
00:07:18,346 --> 00:07:21,305
so the medicine tastes bitter,
and I can't swallow it.

90
00:07:23,185 --> 00:07:24,945
Can you get me some candied fruit?

91
00:07:25,745 --> 00:07:28,706
Okay, I will go out and buy it for you.

92
00:07:58,425 --> 00:07:59,385
Zhao Yucheng.

93
00:08:00,666 --> 00:08:01,786
Zhao Yucheng.

94
00:08:03,706 --> 00:08:04,745
What are you doing here again?

95
00:08:06,305 --> 00:08:07,945
You can't go in.

96
00:08:08,185 --> 00:08:09,146
Meng wan.

97
00:08:09,706 --> 00:08:10,625
Why?

98
00:08:11,106 --> 00:08:12,226
Why?

99
00:08:12,825 --> 00:08:14,226
What are you doing?

100
00:08:16,986 --> 00:08:19,466
You're a woman.

101
00:08:20,346 --> 00:08:21,906
You wouldn't understand
even if I explained.

102
00:08:22,586 --> 00:08:25,226
A man who wants
to succeed should use tricks.

103
00:08:25,586 --> 00:08:27,986
Necessary sacrifices are inevitable.

104
00:08:28,385 --> 00:08:30,026
So you teamed up with Wu Lian

105
00:08:31,026 --> 00:08:32,426
and sold me out?

106
00:08:32,706 --> 00:08:35,505
What makes you say that?

107
00:08:35,946 --> 00:08:38,186
He and I just
take advantage of each other.

108
00:08:38,426 --> 00:08:39,385
Shameless!

109
00:08:40,226 --> 00:08:41,865
You told me

110
00:08:42,785 --> 00:08:45,346
being a litigator is to seek justice.

111
00:08:46,226 --> 00:08:47,385
Pah!

112
00:08:49,306 --> 00:08:50,385
You know what?

113
00:08:51,025 --> 00:08:52,865
Your mother always wanted you
to marry me.

114
00:08:53,066 --> 00:08:53,826
You wish.

115
00:08:54,865 --> 00:08:56,986
I dare not marry a woman

116
00:08:57,145 --> 00:08:58,306
from Yanyu Tower.

117
00:08:59,385 --> 00:09:02,986
However, considering your help for me,

118
00:09:03,625 --> 00:09:05,466
I might consider taking you
as a concubine.

119
00:09:07,505 --> 00:09:11,706
Zhao Yucheng,
you will get your retribution.

120
00:09:12,346 --> 00:09:14,785
Retribution? What retribution?

121
00:09:15,106 --> 00:09:17,745
Did Mr. Wu get any retribution?

122
00:09:18,665 --> 00:09:20,865
In this world, winner takes all.

123
00:09:21,265 --> 00:09:23,426
What's wrong with me
looking out for myself?

124
00:09:24,665 --> 00:09:25,545
Enough.

125
00:09:25,745 --> 00:09:27,706
If there's nothing else,

126
00:09:28,346 --> 00:09:29,145
please leave.

127
00:09:29,176 --> 00:09:29,785
Go.

128
00:09:29,944 --> 00:09:30,905
Don't touch me.

129
00:09:32,106 --> 00:09:32,986
I can leave.

130
00:09:33,625 --> 00:09:37,826
I am waiting for the day you fall.

131
00:09:40,145 --> 00:09:41,145
Fine, we'll see.

132
00:09:41,665 --> 00:09:42,745
See you.

133
00:09:50,306 --> 00:09:50,905
Rulan.

134
00:09:50,946 --> 00:09:51,586
Coming.

135
00:09:52,025 --> 00:09:52,745
Rulan.

136
00:09:55,385 --> 00:09:57,545
How is Rulan?

137
00:09:58,426 --> 00:09:59,545
You better go check on her.

138
00:09:59,986 --> 00:10:01,025
You help me persuade her.

139
00:10:37,106 --> 00:10:37,826
Rulan.

140
00:10:39,946 --> 00:10:40,905
You're really here.

141
00:10:42,145 --> 00:10:43,066
What are you doing here?

142
00:10:43,586 --> 00:10:45,066
Do you still have anything to say?

143
00:10:45,426 --> 00:10:47,706
She almost destroyed me yesterday.

144
00:10:48,466 --> 00:10:50,025
Did you plan

145
00:10:50,385 --> 00:10:51,826
to push everyone else out

146
00:10:52,066 --> 00:10:53,025
while you hide behind?

147
00:10:53,905 --> 00:10:54,785
You ask her.

148
00:10:55,066 --> 00:10:56,306
What did she say to me back then?

149
00:10:59,865 --> 00:11:01,426
You were quite talkative that day.

150
00:11:01,986 --> 00:11:03,265
Are you dumb now?

151
00:11:03,586 --> 00:11:05,066
Make a scene somewhere else.

152
00:11:05,905 --> 00:11:07,145
Your good friend

153
00:11:07,505 --> 00:11:09,066
can only talk something nice,

154
00:11:09,826 --> 00:11:12,265
but in reality, she's useless.

155
00:11:12,745 --> 00:11:13,785
Where was she when you were

156
00:11:13,946 --> 00:11:14,905
in court yesterday?

157
00:11:15,745 --> 00:11:16,745
If I were you,

158
00:11:17,226 --> 00:11:18,505
I would stay away from her.

159
00:11:19,066 --> 00:11:21,586
Or you will get screwed.

160
00:11:22,106 --> 00:11:24,186
Yes, I did betray your trust yesterday.

161
00:11:27,826 --> 00:11:29,106
You're a smart person.

162
00:11:30,826 --> 00:11:32,785
You knew the truth about Wu Lian,

163
00:11:34,106 --> 00:11:36,186
but you didn't dare to speak.

164
00:11:37,025 --> 00:11:38,625
You're just a coward.

165
00:11:43,665 --> 00:11:44,826
If you make a fuss here,

166
00:11:44,986 --> 00:11:46,466
I'll throw you out.

167
00:11:47,025 --> 00:11:48,745
You're still defending her?

168
00:11:48,905 --> 00:11:49,706
Get lost!

169
00:11:56,385 --> 00:11:57,826
You deserve to lose so badly.

170
00:12:06,130 --> 00:12:07,051
Are you okay?

171
00:12:15,890 --> 00:12:16,931
She's right.

172
00:12:18,410 --> 00:12:19,931
I caused you in trouble.

173
00:12:23,770 --> 00:12:24,650
No.

174
00:12:25,730 --> 00:12:27,291
I'm glad you weren't

175
00:12:28,211 --> 00:12:29,530
in court yesterday.

176
00:12:30,931 --> 00:12:32,610
I just never expected

177
00:12:34,250 --> 00:12:35,410
I would lose.

178
00:12:36,931 --> 00:12:38,691
Forget it.

179
00:12:41,091 --> 00:12:42,931
Let's leave here.

180
00:12:44,770 --> 00:12:47,490
Yes, let's leave here.

181
00:12:47,530 --> 00:12:49,051
Go to a beautiful place.

182
00:12:49,091 --> 00:12:49,931
The further, the better.

183
00:12:50,010 --> 00:12:51,171
We can embroider.

184
00:12:51,250 --> 00:12:52,770
We can support ourselves.

185
00:12:53,451 --> 00:12:55,010
Even if we never marry,

186
00:12:55,010 --> 00:12:56,490
we can rely on each other.

187
00:12:58,642 --> 00:13:00,162
I know you want justice,

188
00:13:00,682 --> 00:13:02,402
but don't you understand by now?

189
00:13:02,682 --> 00:13:04,483
Not all grievances will be redressed.

190
00:13:04,642 --> 00:13:07,363
And not all villains will be punished.

191
00:13:08,603 --> 00:13:10,963
You have to think about yourself.

192
00:13:12,922 --> 00:13:13,723
Or have you decided

193
00:13:16,042 --> 00:13:19,642
to stay and marry Wu Lian?

194
00:13:23,723 --> 00:13:25,323
No, I'd rather die.

195
00:13:25,802 --> 00:13:27,562
Is it worth dying for such a man?

196
00:13:28,323 --> 00:13:29,243
He's to blame.

197
00:13:29,282 --> 00:13:32,042
Why should we bear it?

198
00:13:33,483 --> 00:13:34,922
But you're not like me.

199
00:13:35,363 --> 00:13:37,723
You still have a chance
to choose the life you want.

200
00:13:37,963 --> 00:13:41,123
What I just said is the life I want.

201
00:13:57,963 --> 00:14:00,762
Alright, let's get out of here.

202
00:14:01,162 --> 00:14:02,363
The further we go, the better.

203
00:14:08,434 --> 00:14:09,195
In the next few days,

204
00:14:10,355 --> 00:14:11,434
you should eat well

205
00:14:11,794 --> 00:14:12,634
and keep healthy.

206
00:14:13,034 --> 00:14:14,115
Since we've decided to leave,

207
00:14:14,794 --> 00:14:15,914
we must do some preparations.

208
00:14:16,235 --> 00:14:17,154
Wait for my news.

209
00:14:32,475 --> 00:14:33,434
Where did you get this?

210
00:14:33,914 --> 00:14:36,875
I sold my jewelry a few days ago

211
00:14:37,034 --> 00:14:38,634
to find a litigator.

212
00:14:40,235 --> 00:14:41,754
Finally, it comes in handy.

213
00:14:47,674 --> 00:14:48,514
Okay.

214
00:14:54,930 --> 00:14:56,754
(Yanyu Tower)

215
00:15:02,754 --> 00:15:03,554
By the way, Ling,

216
00:15:03,875 --> 00:15:05,195
I'm about to finish the book

217
00:15:05,355 --> 00:15:07,274
you recommended us. It's a good book.

218
00:15:07,835 --> 00:15:08,434
Isn't it?

219
00:15:08,475 --> 00:15:09,875
I have many good books.

220
00:15:10,115 --> 00:15:11,514
You can get them from me.

221
00:15:11,514 --> 00:15:13,554
Okay, we'll go.

222
00:15:13,794 --> 00:15:14,475
See you tomorrow.

223
00:15:14,715 --> 00:15:15,674
See you tomorrow.

224
00:15:37,115 --> 00:15:37,914
Mr. Wu.

225
00:15:39,315 --> 00:15:41,595
How is the embroidery piece
from yesterday?

226
00:15:42,475 --> 00:15:43,434
I've revised it many times,

227
00:15:43,754 --> 00:15:45,355
but it's still not good enough.

228
00:15:46,674 --> 00:15:48,075
If you have any problems,

229
00:15:48,434 --> 00:15:49,715
you can come to me anytime.

230
00:15:50,154 --> 00:15:50,995
Thank you.

231
00:16:01,434 --> 00:16:02,195
You may go.

232
00:16:03,315 --> 00:16:03,995
Alright.

233
00:16:21,674 --> 00:16:22,875
Let's drink.

234
00:16:25,715 --> 00:16:27,154
Is it Mr. Li?

235
00:16:31,995 --> 00:16:33,554
As the usual.

236
00:16:34,674 --> 00:16:36,355
He's a poor guy.

237
00:16:37,434 --> 00:16:40,195
Did you just see your sweetheart again?

238
00:16:40,875 --> 00:16:41,634
I'm telling you.

239
00:16:42,274 --> 00:16:44,195
It is useless.

240
00:16:44,794 --> 00:16:47,154
A suitable marriage is
about the match of two families.

241
00:16:50,034 --> 00:16:50,835
Here.

242
00:16:51,394 --> 00:16:52,195
It's on credit.

243
00:16:53,634 --> 00:16:55,355
You should pay off all your debts.

244
00:16:56,514 --> 00:16:58,595
I will settle it
at the end of the month.

245
00:16:59,274 --> 00:17:00,075
Fine.

246
00:17:09,555 --> 00:17:10,994
Isn't this Butcher Du?

247
00:17:11,434 --> 00:17:12,994
I heard your butcher shop is doing well.

248
00:17:13,755 --> 00:17:15,035
Of course.

249
00:17:15,355 --> 00:17:16,315
Good.

250
00:17:16,555 --> 00:17:18,355
You asked me
to write a letter to your lover.

251
00:17:18,355 --> 00:17:20,234
It costs ten copper coins.

252
00:17:20,434 --> 00:17:21,234
You haven't paid me yet.

253
00:17:21,394 --> 00:17:22,434
Since we meet today,

254
00:17:22,434 --> 00:17:23,555
why don't you settle it?

255
00:17:23,595 --> 00:17:24,674
What letter?

256
00:17:25,315 --> 00:17:26,355
If you don't remember,

257
00:17:26,515 --> 00:17:27,115
I'll recall.

258
00:17:27,315 --> 00:17:28,355
You asked me to write...

259
00:17:28,394 --> 00:17:30,394
Just a letter.

260
00:17:30,714 --> 00:17:32,875
Is it worth ten copper coins?

261
00:17:33,115 --> 00:17:35,154
It's a rip-off.

262
00:17:36,674 --> 00:17:37,914
I was just saying.

263
00:17:38,194 --> 00:17:39,914
I don't dare to let you pay.

264
00:17:42,474 --> 00:17:43,394
Just ignore him.

265
00:17:43,555 --> 00:17:47,115
Sir, I'll pay for today's wine.

266
00:18:27,595 --> 00:18:28,515
I'm back.

267
00:18:31,075 --> 00:18:31,994
Wan.

268
00:18:56,154 --> 00:18:56,994
Wan.

269
00:19:00,035 --> 00:19:02,555
Wan, why is the door bolted?

270
00:19:03,275 --> 00:19:04,355
I'm getting changed.

271
00:19:15,154 --> 00:19:17,835
Wan, if you still want to run out,

272
00:19:18,194 --> 00:19:20,075
I have to lock you in the room.

273
00:19:21,234 --> 00:19:22,075
I know.

274
00:19:24,634 --> 00:19:25,994
Fortunately, your father

275
00:19:26,555 --> 00:19:28,634
has been drinking outside
and hasn't come home these days.

276
00:19:29,394 --> 00:19:30,595
Otherwise, if he saw you

277
00:19:31,154 --> 00:19:33,795
and smelled the medicine,
he would be suspicious.

278
00:19:34,634 --> 00:19:36,595
If he knew I sent you
to the embroidery house

279
00:19:36,795 --> 00:19:37,835
and you caused trouble,

280
00:19:38,755 --> 00:19:40,515
neither of us would have a good life.

281
00:19:49,394 --> 00:19:50,234
Mother.

282
00:19:51,954 --> 00:19:53,275
Have you ever thought about a divorce?

283
00:19:54,875 --> 00:19:56,275
What are you talking about?

284
